{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Many believe driving is an activity"},{"time":3000,"text":"solely reserved for those who can see."},{"time":5000,"text":"A blind person driving a vehicle safely and independently"},{"time":8000,"text":"was thought to be an impossible task, until now."},{"time":11000,"text":"Hello, my name is Dennis Hong,"},{"time":13000,"text":"and we're bringing freedom and independence to the blind"},{"time":15000,"text":"by building a vehicle for the visually impaired."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"So before I talk about this car for the blind,"},{"time":21000,"text":"let me briefly tell you about another project that I worked on"},{"time":23000,"text":"called the DARPA Urban Challenge."},{"time":25000,"text":"Now this was about building a robotic car"},{"time":27000,"text":"that can drive itself."},{"time":29000,"text":"You press start, nobody touches anything,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and it can reach its destination fully autonomously."},{"time":34000,"text":"So in 2007, our team won half a million dollars"},{"time":37000,"text":"by placing third place in this competition."},{"time":39000,"text":"So about that time,"},{"time":41000,"text":"the National Federation of the Blind, or NFB,"},{"time":43000,"text":"challenged the research committee"},{"time":45000,"text":"about who can develop a car"},{"time":47000,"text":"that lets a blind person drive safely and independently."},{"time":49000,"text":"We decided to give it a try,"},{"time":51000,"text":"because we thought, \"Hey, how hard could it be?\""},{"time":53000,"text":"We have already an autonomous vehicle."},{"time":55000,"text":"We just put a blind person in it and we're done, right?"},{"time":57000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":59000,"text":"We couldn't have been more wrong."},{"time":61000,"text":"What NFB wanted"},{"time":63000,"text":"was not a vehicle that can drive a blind person around,"},{"time":66000,"text":"but a vehicle where a blind person can make active decisions and drive."},{"time":69000,"text":"So we had to throw everything out the window"},{"time":71000,"text":"and start from scratch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73000,"text":"So to test this crazy idea,"},{"time":75000,"text":"we developed a small dune buggy prototype vehicle"},{"time":77000,"text":"to test the feasibility."},{"time":79000,"text":"And in the summer of 2009,"},{"time":81000,"text":"we invited dozens of blind youth from all over the country"},{"time":84000,"text":"and gave them a chance to take it for a spin."},{"time":86000,"text":"It was an absolutely amazing experience."},{"time":88000,"text":"But the problem with this car was"},{"time":90000,"text":"it was designed to only be driven in a very controlled environment,"},{"time":93000,"text":"in a flat, closed-off parking lot --"},{"time":95000,"text":"even the lanes defined by red traffic cones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"So with this success,"},{"time":99000,"text":"we decided to take the next big step,"},{"time":101000,"text":"to develop a real car that can be driven on real roads."},{"time":104000,"text":"So how does it work?"},{"time":106000,"text":"Well, it's a rather complex system,"},{"time":108000,"text":"but let me try to explain it, maybe simplify it."},{"time":111000,"text":"So we have three steps."},{"time":113000,"text":"We have perception, computation"},{"time":115000,"text":"and non-visual interfaces."},{"time":117000,"text":"Now obviously the driver cannot see,"},{"time":119000,"text":"so the system needs to perceive the environment"},{"time":121000,"text":"and gather information for the driver."},{"time":123000,"text":"For that, we use an initial measurement unit."},{"time":126000,"text":"So it measures acceleration, angular acceleration --"},{"time":128000,"text":"like a human ear, inner ear."},{"time":130000,"text":"We fuse that information with a GPS unit"},{"time":132000,"text":"to get an estimate of the location of the car."},{"time":135000,"text":"We also use two cameras to detect the lanes of the road."},{"time":138000,"text":"And we also use three laser range finders."},{"time":140000,"text":"The lasers scan the environment to detect obstacles --"},{"time":143000,"text":"a car approaching from the front, the back"},{"time":145000,"text":"and also any obstacles that run into the roads,"},{"time":148000,"text":"any obstacles around the vehicle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"So all this vast amount of information is then fed into the computer,"},{"time":153000,"text":"and the computer can do two things."},{"time":155000,"text":"One is, first of all, process this information"},{"time":158000,"text":"to have an understanding of the environment --"},{"time":160000,"text":"these are the lanes of the road, there's the obstacles --"},{"time":163000,"text":"and convey this information to the driver."},{"time":165000,"text":"The system is also smart enough"},{"time":167000,"text":"to figure out the safest way to operate the car."},{"time":169000,"text":"So we can also generate instructions"},{"time":171000,"text":"on how to operate the controls of the vehicle."},{"time":173000,"text":"But the problem is this: How do we convey"},{"time":175000,"text":"this information and instructions"},{"time":177000,"text":"to a person who cannot see"},{"time":179000,"text":"fast enough and accurate enough so he can drive?"},{"time":182000,"text":"So for this, we developed many different types"},{"time":184000,"text":"of non-visual user interface technology."},{"time":187000,"text":"So starting from a three-dimensional ping sound system,"},{"time":189000,"text":"a vibrating vest,"},{"time":191000,"text":"a click wheel with voice commands, a leg strip,"},{"time":194000,"text":"even a shoe that applies pressure to the foot."},{"time":196000,"text":"But today we're going to talk about"},{"time":198000,"text":"three of these non-visual user interfaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"Now the first interface is called a DriveGrip."},{"time":203000,"text":"So these are a pair of gloves,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and it has vibrating elements on the knuckle part"},{"time":207000,"text":"so you can convey instructions about how to steer --"},{"time":210000,"text":"the direction and the intensity."},{"time":212000,"text":"Another device is called SpeedStrip."},{"time":214000,"text":"So this is a chair -- as a matter of fact, it's actually a massage chair."},{"time":217000,"text":"We gut it out, and we rearrange the vibrating elements in different patterns,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and we actuate them to convey information about the speed,"},{"time":224000,"text":"and also instructions how to use the gas and the brake pedal."},{"time":227000,"text":"So over here, you can see"},{"time":229000,"text":"how the computer understands the environment,"},{"time":231000,"text":"and because you cannot see the vibration,"},{"time":233000,"text":"we actually put red LED's on the driver so that you can see what's happening."},{"time":236000,"text":"This is the sensory data,"},{"time":238000,"text":"and that data is transferred to the devices through the computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"So these two devices, DriveGrip and SpeedStrip,"},{"time":243000,"text":"are very effective."},{"time":245000,"text":"But the problem is"},{"time":247000,"text":"these are instructional cue devices."},{"time":249000,"text":"So this is not really freedom, right?"},{"time":251000,"text":"The computer tells you how to drive --"},{"time":253000,"text":"turn left, turn right, speed up, stop."},{"time":255000,"text":"We call this the \"backseat-driver problem.\""},{"time":257000,"text":"So we're moving away from the instructional cue devices,"},{"time":260000,"text":"and we're now focusing more"},{"time":262000,"text":"on the informational devices."},{"time":264000,"text":"A good example for this informational non-visual user interface"},{"time":266000,"text":"is called AirPix."},{"time":268000,"text":"So think of it as a monitor for the blind."},{"time":270000,"text":"So it's a small tablet, has many holes in it,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and compressed air comes out,"},{"time":274000,"text":"so it can actually draw images."},{"time":276000,"text":"So even though you are blind, you can put your hand over it,"},{"time":278000,"text":"you can see the lanes of the road and obstacles."},{"time":280000,"text":"Actually, you can also change the frequency of the air coming out"},{"time":283000,"text":"and possibly the temperature."},{"time":285000,"text":"So it's actually a multi-dimensional user interface."},{"time":288000,"text":"So here you can see the left camera, the right camera from the vehicle"},{"time":291000,"text":"and how the computer interprets that and sends that information to the AirPix."},{"time":294000,"text":"For this, we're showing a simulator,"},{"time":296000,"text":"a blind person driving using the AirPix."},{"time":299000,"text":"This simulator was also very useful for training the blind drivers"},{"time":302000,"text":"and also quickly testing different types of ideas"},{"time":304000,"text":"for different types of non-visual user interfaces."},{"time":306000,"text":"So basically that's how it works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308000,"text":"So just a month ago,"},{"time":310000,"text":"on January 29th,"},{"time":312000,"text":"we unveiled this vehicle for the very first time to the public"},{"time":314000,"text":"at the world-famous Daytona International Speedway"},{"time":317000,"text":"during the Rolex 24 racing event."},{"time":319000,"text":"We also had some surprises. Let's take a look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"(Video) Announcer: This is an historic day in January."},{"time":336000,"text":"He's coming up to the grandstand, fellow Federationists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340000,"text":"(Cheering)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"(Honking)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"There's the grandstand now."},{"time":351000,"text":"And he's [unclear] following that van that's out in front of him."},{"time":355000,"text":"Well there comes the first box."},{"time":357000,"text":"Now let's see if Mark avoids it."},{"time":360000,"text":"He does. He passes it on the right."},{"time":365000,"text":"Third box is out. The fourth box is out."},{"time":368000,"text":"And he's perfectly making his way between the two."},{"time":371000,"text":"He's closing in on the van"},{"time":373000,"text":"to make the moving pass."},{"time":377000,"text":"Well this is what it's all about,"},{"time":379000,"text":"this kind of dynamic display of audacity and ingenuity."},{"time":384000,"text":"He's approaching the end of the run,"},{"time":387000,"text":"makes his way between the barrels that are set up there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392000,"text":"(Honking)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"Dennis Hong: I'm so happy for you."},{"time":403000,"text":"Mark's going to give me a ride back to the hotel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"Mark Riccobono: Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"DH: So since we started this project,"},{"time":421000,"text":"we've been getting hundreds of letters, emails, phone calls"},{"time":424000,"text":"from people from all around the world."},{"time":426000,"text":"Letters thanking us, but sometimes you also get funny letters like this one:"},{"time":429000,"text":"\"Now I understand why there is Braille on a drive-up ATM machine.\""},{"time":433000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":435000,"text":"But sometimes --"},{"time":437000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":439000,"text":"But sometimes I also do get --"},{"time":441000,"text":"I wouldn't call it hate mail --"},{"time":443000,"text":"but letters of really strong concern:"},{"time":445000,"text":"\"Dr. Hong, are you insane,"},{"time":447000,"text":"trying to put blind people on the road?"},{"time":449000,"text":"You must be out of your mind.\""},{"time":451000,"text":"But this vehicle is a prototype vehicle,"},{"time":453000,"text":"and it's not going to be on the road"},{"time":455000,"text":"until it's proven as safe as, or safer than, today's vehicle."},{"time":457000,"text":"And I truly believe that this can happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460000,"text":"But still, will the society,"},{"time":462000,"text":"would they accept such a radical idea?"},{"time":464000,"text":"How are we going to handle insurance?"},{"time":466000,"text":"How are we going to issue driver's licenses?"},{"time":468000,"text":"There's many of these different kinds of hurdles besides technology challenges"},{"time":471000,"text":"that we need to address before this becomes a reality."},{"time":474000,"text":"Of course, the main goal of this project"},{"time":476000,"text":"is to develop a car for the blind."},{"time":478000,"text":"But potentially more important than this"},{"time":480000,"text":"is the tremendous value of the spin-off technology"},{"time":483000,"text":"that can come from this project."},{"time":485000,"text":"The sensors that are used can see through the dark,"},{"time":487000,"text":"the fog and rain."},{"time":489000,"text":"And together with this new type of interfaces,"},{"time":491000,"text":"we can use these technologies"},{"time":493000,"text":"and apply them to safer cars for sighted people."},{"time":495000,"text":"Or for the blind, everyday home appliances --"},{"time":498000,"text":"in the educational setting, in the office setting."},{"time":500000,"text":"Just imagine, in a classroom a teacher writes on the blackboard"},{"time":503000,"text":"and a blind student can see what's written and read"},{"time":506000,"text":"using these non-visual interfaces."},{"time":508000,"text":"This is priceless."},{"time":511000,"text":"So today, the things I've showed you today, is just the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}